cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language understanding (NLU) and text classification, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques and benchmarks state-of-the-art models, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with associating appropriate labels with text. Lastly, the paper discusses the use of textual entailment formulation, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
